T1  - From Bottom of the Barrel to Cream of the Crop: Sequential Screening With Positive Selection
AU  - Tirole, Jean
Y1  - 2016/07/01
PY  - 2016
DA  - 2016/07/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.3982/ECTA12961
T2  - Econometrica
JF  - Econometrica
JO  - Econometrica
JA  - Econometrica
SP  - 1291
EP  - 1343
VL  - 84
IS  - 4
KW  - Repeated relationships
KW  - screening
KW  - positive selection
KW  - time consistency
KW  - shifting preferences
KW  - exit games
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0012-9682
UR  - https://doi.org/10.3982/ECTA12961
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - In a number of interesting environments, dynamic screening involves positive selection: in contrast with Coasian dynamics, only the most motivated remain over time. The paper provides conditions under which the principal's commitment optimum is time consistent and uses this result to derive testable predictions under permanent or transient shocks. It also identifies environments in which time consistency does not hold despite positive selection, and yet simple equilibrium characterizations can be obtained.
ER  - 

